An open-source multimedia framework for audio/video processing.
Website: https://ffmpeg.org

yt-dlp - Licensed under The Unlicense (Public Domain)
An open-source command-line tool for downloading media.
Website: https://github.com/yt-dlp/yt-dlp

Users should review and comply with the licensing terms of these components.

================================================================================
4. DATA HANDLING
================================================================================

Your preferences and usage data are stored securely to enable features like 
settings sync and progress tracking.

WHAT MEDIO STORES:

  - Settings: Format preferences, buffer size, codec choices
  - Statistics: Download counts and total data processed
  - Progress: Experience points, level, and rank
  - History: Download URLs and titles (if history tracking is enabled)
  - License: Current license type and activation status
  - Avatar: Your profile image (if uploaded)

WHAT MEDIO DOES NOT STORE:

  - Names, emails, addresses, or phone numbers
  - Payment information (handled securely by Stripe)
  - The actual content of downloaded files
  - Your browsing activity outside of Medio

PRIVACY CONTROLS:

You have control over your data:

  - Disable history tracking: Settings > Advanced > History Tracking > Disabled
  - Delete individual history entries via right-click in the History tab
  - Delete your account: Navigate to Settings and scroll to the Delete Account button

DATA RETENTION:

  - Basic accounts: Automatically deleted after 365 days of inactivity
  - Premium accounts: Retained while license is active

================================================================================
5. AVATAR GUIDELINES
================================================================================

Uploaded profile images must not contain explicit, violent, or inappropriate 
content. The Author reserves the right to remove violating avatars and may 
suspend accounts for repeated violations.

